Kendoo, the slot provider, is looking for a talented professional to join the dynamic studio behind its games as a Python Developer.

Our team of passionate and talented professionals brings unique visions to life, aiming to positively impact the iGaming industry. We are thrilled about the work we do and are excited to welcome new members to join us on our mission.

The following skills are important to us:
– Knowledge of modern Python (3.x);
– Python development experience — at least 1 year;
– Confident understanding of OOP with functional programming elements;
– Understanding of client-server architecture;
– At least B1 English level (spoken and written). 

Will be a plus:
– Experience in slot game development;
– Knowledge of probability theory and combinatorics;
– Experience with version control systems (e.g., Git).

Your future responsibilities:
– Develop backend logic for casino slot game modules.
– Implement a bot that simulates player actions multiple times and gathers statistical data.
– Integrate testing tools into the game module to enhance debugging and quality assurance.
– Implement and integrate new features into the game.
– Optimize and refine game mechanics based on simulation results.
– Collaborate with the team to ensure smooth integration and performance of backend components.
– Maintain and improve code efficiency for scalability and reliability.



What we offer:
You will enjoy corporate benefits, like:
— Health Insurance: We care about the well-being of our team members and offer comprehensive insurance coverage for both domestic and international needs.
— Corporate English Classes: We believe in enhancing your communication skills. Take advantage of our corporate English classes to further develop your language proficiency.
— Well-being support: The ability to choose a psychologist on the platform we partner with to get support and guidance whenever you need it.
— Flexible schedule: You will have the opportunity to choose where you want to work — at one of our comfortable offices or from home. We ensure comprehensive company-paid 21 paid days off during the year; unlimited sick leaves, and you can request an unpaid leave of absence.
— We are committed to fostering the professional growth of our team members. As part of our commitment to your development, we provide a customized growth plan for each team member. This plan is meticulously crafted, taking into account your unique strengths, areas for development, and aspirations for career excellence, all in alignment with our company's objectives.

